      "**Industries that benefit most.** AI receptionists deliver the highest ROI in high-volume, appointment-driven businesses: medical and dental clinics (managing bookings, prescription refill requests, and appointment reminders), law firms (intake qualification and consultation scheduling), hair and beauty salons (booking management and reminder sequences), real estate agencies (enquiry qualification and viewing scheduling), and coaching businesses (discovery call booking and onboarding workflows). Any business receiving more than 20 inbound calls per day will see measurable returns within weeks.",
      "**How the AI gets better over time.** Unlike a rigid phone menu, a well-built AI receptionist learns from every interaction. Call transcripts are reviewed weekly for mishandled queries — the knowledge base is updated, edge cases are addressed, and prompts are refined. After 4–8 weeks of operation, most AI receptionists handle 85–92% of inbound calls without escalation. The learning curve is managed, not outsourced — we include a 60-day optimisation period in every deployment we deliver.",
      "**Cost comparison: AI receptionist vs human staff.** A full-time human receptionist in India costs ₹20,000–₹35,000 per month in salary alone, works 8 hours a day, 5 days a week, and handles one call at a time. An AI receptionist costs ₹4,000–₹8,000 per month, operates 24/7, handles unlimited simultaneous calls, never calls in sick, and never needs training updates beyond a prompt edit. The payback period on a typical deployment is 6–10 weeks.",
      "**Integration with your existing tech stack.** AI receptionists connect with your existing tools to deliver real value. Calendar integration covers Google Calendar, Microsoft Outlook, Calendly, and practice management software like Cliniko or Practo. CRM integration covers HubSpot, Zoho, Salesforce, and industry-specific platforms. Communication follow-ups go via SMS through Twilio and WhatsApp through the Business API. Most telephony platforms also support call recording and transcription for quality review and compliance purposes.",
      "**Getting started with an AI receptionist.** The first step is a knowledge audit — documenting everything your human receptionist currently knows: your services, pricing, booking logic, FAQs, escalation triggers, and tone of voice. This becomes the AI's knowledge base. Next, we configure the voice, set up the telephony number, connect your calendar and CRM, and run through 50+ test call scenarios before go-live. Most deployments are live and handling real calls within 2–3 weeks. Contact [HowAutomate](https://howautomate.com) to start your AI receptionist project today.",
