      "**The four-week onboarding process.** **Week 1:** Audit existing marketing activities and identify the highest-impact automation targets. **Week 2:** Set up data connections and build the agent's knowledge base — brand voice, product details, ICP definition, competitive positioning. **Week 3:** Deploy the first agent (typically content generation or ad optimisation), run in parallel with existing processes to validate quality. **Week 4:** Go live and establish a weekly review cadence for continuous improvement.",
      "**Common pitfalls to avoid.** Marketing AI agents fail when: the knowledge base is too thin, oversight is removed too early (agents need human review for the first 4–6 weeks), and success is measured by activity instead of outcomes (more content is worthless if it doesn't convert). The businesses that see the best results treat their marketing AI agent as a team member that needs onboarding, feedback, and ongoing direction — not a set-it-and-forget-it tool. Ready to build yours? Visit [howautomate.com](https://howautomate.com).",
